    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-08T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/15181: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-08T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 8, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 8—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>576. Reference Department’s 186, July 7, 8 p.m., for Tokyo. I have taken action
                    as requested in last paragraph of this message. At the same time I have informed
                    Japanese Consul General that, according to information from the Commander of the
                    Yangtze Patrol, five bombs struck within two hundred yards of the U. S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Tutuila</hi> at Chungking during the recent air raids there.
                    Commander Yangtze Patrol has made representations to senior Japanese naval
                    officer here but I have deemed it appropriate to add this information in my
                    representations to the Japanese Consul General, and the Embassy at Tokyo may
                    wish to do likewise.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo, Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
